The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 December is 119,312 (13,751.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 02 December, there were 5,703 new confirmed cases (657.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 25 November, there were 5,618 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 2% (85 extra cases).
